Sentencas: Highly asymmetric yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) hollow fibre membranes were fabricated by a modified phase inversion and sintering technique using a mixture of NMP and water as internal coagulant.
Titulo: Highly asymmetric yttria stabilized zirconia hollow fibre membranes

Sentencas: The obtained YSZ hollow fibres possess a thin dense outer skin layer of thickness 3-5 mu m and a thicker porous sub-layer with a surface porosity of 28.8%.
Titulo: Highly asymmetric yttria stabilized zirconia hollow fibre membranes

Sentencas: The crystal phase of the YSZ hollow fibres retains the same cubic fluorite structure as the original YSZ powders after the spinning and sintering process.
Titulo: Highly asymmetric yttria stabilized zirconia hollow fibre membranes

Sentencas: The thin dense skin layer is integrated perfectly with the porous layer and is especially suitable for use as an electrolyte film in micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Highly asymmetric yttria stabilized zirconia hollow fibre membranes
